main_body:
Tenders shall be valid only if they are accompanied by:
(a) proof that the tenderer has lodged a tender security which, notwithstanding Article 13(4) of Regulation (EEC) No 2131/93, shall be set at EUR 10 per tonne;
(b) a written undertaking from the tenderer to use the cereals to feed animals or to incorporate it into animal feed before 30 April 2004 and to lodge a security of EUR 30 per tonne no later than two working days after the day on which the declaration of award of the tender is received;
(c) a commitment to keep stock accounts enabling verification that the rye has indeed been incorporated into animal feed.
